Class ZipDataSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.media.protocol.DataSource
      • javax.media.protocol.PullBufferDataSource

    javax.media.Controls, javax.media.Duration, javax.media.protocol.Controls
    public class ZipDataSource
extends javax.media.protocol.PullBufferDataSource
    A custom data source for extracting frames of an animation from a Zip file.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ZipDataSource

        public ZipDataSource​(java.io.File zipFile,
                     SvgPanel svgPanel)
        Creates a new ZipDataSource containing a single ZipSourceStream. The provided svgPanel is used to render SVG documents contained in zipFile. To check if the file is valid, use the isValidSource() method.
        Parameters:
        zipFile - The archive containing the frames of the animation.
        svgPanel - The SvgPanel used to render frames of the animation.

    • Method Detail

      • setOutputFile

        public void setOutputFile​(java.io.File file)
        Sets a reference to the output file used during export. MovieGenerator will delete this file if the export is cancelled.

      • getOutputFile

        public java.io.File getOutputFile()
        Gets the output file used during export.

      • getFrameCount

        public int getFrameCount()
        Returns the number of frames in the source animation.

      • getCurrentFrame

        public int getCurrentFrame()
        Returns the index of the next frame to be rendered by the ZipSourceStream contained in this ZipDataSource. For example, a value of 0 means that the stream has been reset, and the next frame it renders will be the first.

      • advanceFrame

        public boolean advanceFrame()
        Manually renders the next frame. This is used in playback.
        Returns:
        True if the next frame is valid and rendered. False otherwise.

      • seekToFrame

        public boolean seekToFrame​(int frame)
        Manually seek to a certain frame and render it.
        Returns:
        True if the desired frame is valid and rendered. False otherwise.

      • flushStream

        public boolean flushStream()
        Flushes the stream. This is similiar in concept to rewinding.
        Returns:
        True if the stream is flushed, false otherwise (extremely unlikely).

      • setStartTimeIndex

        public boolean setStartTimeIndex​(int index)
        Sets the frame index with which to start all renderings. Any seeks to frames before this index will return false.
        Parameters:
        index - The frame index with which export and playback should begin.
        Returns:
        True if index is valid, false otherwise.

      • setEndTimeIndex

        public boolean setEndTimeIndex​(int index)
        Sets the frame index with which to end all renderings. Any seeks to frames after this index will return false.
        Parameters:
        index - The frame index with which export and playback should end, inclusive.
        Returns:
        True if index is valid, false otherwise.

      • setTimeFactor

        public void setTimeFactor​(double timeFactor)
        Sets the time factor used to determine the framerate in exported video. Values of 1 correspond to real-time, 0 to 1 (non inclusive) to slower than real-time, and greater than 1 to faster than real-time. Examples: 2.0 corresponds to a speed two times greater than real-time; .5 corresponds to a speed two times slower than real-time.
        Parameters:
        timeFactor - The desired time factor.

      • getMovDimensions

        public java.awt.Dimension getMovDimensions()
        Gets the modified, original dimensions of the SVG animation. The modification comes in terms of forcing the width to the greatest factor of 4 smaller than than or equal to the original value. This is required due to JMF restrictions on image width, as widths by other factors are distorted.

      • getRenderDimensions

        public java.awt.Dimension getRenderDimensions()
        Gets the modified dimensions of the SVG image. They can be any value, but the width should be forced to a whole multiple of 4. This is required due to JMF restrictions on image width, as widths by other factors are distorted.

      • setRenderDimensions

        public void setRenderDimensions​(int renderWidth,
                                int renderHeight)
        Sets the modified dimensions of the SVG image. RenderWidth is forced to the greatest multiple of four less than or equal to the provided value due to JMF restrictions on image width.

      • getTimeStamps

        public double[] getTimeStamps()
        Returns the time stamps built into the file names of the ZIP entries as a double array.
